"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-2024-olympics-learn-five-cool-things-about-tatjana\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis 2024 Olympics: Learn five cool things about Tatjana  Those sporting heroes, phew!  Tatjana Smith already has a gold medal at the Paris 2024 Olympics and she's gunning for another. Learn more about the Team SA star.  Tatjana Smith, previously Schoenmaker when she broke the world record to claim gold in the 200m breaststroke event three years ago in Tokyo in2.18.95, has won gold again. This time, in the 100m event in Paris. 27-year-old Smith won the 100m silver in Japan but wasn't to be denied in 2024, touching the wall first in1.05.28thanks to a massive surge in the final quarter of the race.  Info viaolympics.com'sofficial website.  \\\"Focus on one's improvement and one's own goals rather than comparing oneself to others. If you are constantly improving, you will eventually get to the top. For me, it was always about improving my time.\\\"  Smith stands to become only the second swimmer in history after Penny Heyns in 1996 to complete the 100m and 200m breaststroke golden double at the same Olympics event. She wasn't yet born when Heyns accomplished this historic feat. The 27-year-old contests her 200m breaststroke heat onWednesday 31 July at 11:00 SA timewith thesemi-finals going at 21:51 and 21:58.The finalis onThursday 01 August at 21:04.You know thatNando's will be watching. Smith won this event in Tokyo with a time of2.18.95, a world record which has since been eclipsed by Russian Evgeniia Chikunova in 2023 with a time of2.17.55.Will Smith have taken that personally?  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.com. You can also send a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1. Follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor your social fix.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"